A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Sherilyn P. Bell; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Sherilyn P. Bell is a highly respected healthcare professional whose career
3 spans clinical research, laboratory management, and public health, including five years in
4 stem cell clinical trials and extensive work in high-complexity testing; and
5 WHEREAS, she has demonstrated excellence across multiple leadership roles in laboratory
6 science, including as Laboratory Manager at Response Technologies Inc., Lead Viral Load
7 Technologist at the Public Health Laboratory in Decatur, and Auditor for Patient Service
8 Centers at the Laboratory Corporation of America; and
9 WHEREAS, she has also served as a tireless healthcare advocate both at the United States
10 Capitol and in the State of Georgia through her work with the Lymphedema Advocacy Group
11 and the Lighthouse Lymphedema Network, lobbying alongside the late Congressman John
12 Lewis and other national advocates to push forward critical patient protections; and
13 WHEREAS, through her leadership and persistence, she helped achieve the passage of the
14 U.S. Lymphedema Treatment Act, first introduced in 2010 and passed by Congress on
H. R. 961
